{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, a lack of awareness of the global project context leads to hallucinations, where the model generates code invoking non-existent classes, methods, or variables.",
    "This is a primary cause of compilation errors, with \"symbol not found\" errors accounting for up to 43.6% of such failures in some studies [167].",
    "To resolve this tension, researchers have developed several strategies.",
    "These include static analysis-driven adaptive focal context construction [27], using method slicing and code reduction to pass only the most relevant information [143,167], and even empowering LLMs to actively query missing context definitions via tool functions like get_info [9].",
    "In practice, the availability of surrounding test suite context significantly affects the usability of generated tests, as observed with GitHub Copilot in Python [36]."
  ]
}